erguson, Washington Post reporter Wesley Lowery gives account of his arrest|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/in-ferguson-washington-post-reporter-wesley-lowery-gives-account-of-his-arrest/2014/08/13/0fe25c0e-2359-11e4-86ca-6f03cbd15c1a_story.html?Post+generic=%3Ftid%3Dsm_twitter_washingtonpost|accessdate=2014-08-14|work=The Washington Post|date=2014-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814050801/http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/in-ferguson-washington-post-reporter-wesley-lowery-gives-account-of-his-arrest/2014/08/13/0fe25c0e-2359-11e4-86ca-6f03cbd15c1a_story.html?Post+generic=%3Ftid%3Dsm_twitter_washingtonpost|archive-date=2014-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”

周三晚上，[[半岛电视台|半岛电视台]]美国记者报道弗格森镇的抗议，遭到特警用催泪瓦斯和橡皮子弹攻击。一名警察被拍到后，将记者的摄像机推向地面，并把采访设备拆除<ref>{{cite news|title=Police fire tear gas, stun grenades at Ferguson protesters|url=http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2014/8/13/2nd-shooting-ferguson.html|accessdate=2014-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814235931/http://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2014/8/13/2nd-shooting-ferguson.html|archive-date=2014-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=TV crews hit by bean bags, tear gas|url=http://www.ksdk.com/story/news/local/2014/08/14/crews-hit-with-bean-bags-tear-gas/14042747/|accessdate=2014-08-14|publisher=KSDK|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20140824025609/http://www.ksdk.com/story/news/local/2014/08/14/crews-hit-with-bean-bags-tear-gas/14042747/|archive-date=2014-08-24|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mintpressnews.com/ferguson-police-targeting-media-arrests-tear-gas-blackouts/195327/ |title=Ferguson Police Targeting Media With Arrests, Tear Gas, Bean Bags And Blackouts |publisher=Mintpressnews.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814221622/http://www.mintpressnews.com/ferguson-police-targeting-media-arrests-tear-gas-blackouts/195327/ |archive-date=2014-08-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2014/08/14/police_in_ferguson_tear_gas_tv_reporters_al_jazeera_camera_crew_flees.html|title = Police in Ferguson Tear-Gassed a TV Camera Crew, Then Dismantled Their Equipment|last = Mathis-Lilley|first = Ben|date = 2014-08-14|work = |accessdate = 2014-08-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140815031550/http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2014/08/14/police_in_ferguson_tear_gas_tv_reporters_al_jazeera_camera_crew_flees.html|archive-date = 2014-08-15|dead-url = no}}</ref>。该台美国部发表声明，称“对新闻自由的攻击令人震惊，显然是对我们报道这一重大事件能力的[[寒蝉效应|寒蝉效应]]<ref name="PearsonCabreraShoichetCNN">{{cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2014/08/14/us/missouri-teen-shooting/index.html |title=Missouri state troopers take over security in Ferguson |first1=Michael |last1=Pearson |first2=Ana |last2=Cabrera |first3=Catherine E. |last3=Shoichet |publisher=CNN |date=2014-08-15 |access-date=2014-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821050026/http://www.cnn.com/2014/08/14/us/missouri-teen-shooting/index.html |archive-date=2014-08-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。8月14日，星期四，圣查尔斯县特警队发表新闻稿，指“特警队没有阻止媒体报道，是在记者的同意下才把设备搬走<ref>{{cite news |author=Casey Nolen |publisher=KSDK |date=2014-08-14 |url=http://www.ksdk.com/story/news/local/2014/08/14/crews-hit-with-bean-bags-tear-gas/14042747/ |title=TV crews hit by bean bags, tear gas |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20140824025609/http://www.ksdk.com/story/news/local/2014/08/14/crews-hit-with-bean-bags-tear-gas/14042747/ |archive-date=2014-08-24 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”有清晰视频，捕捉到一辆标有“圣查尔斯县特警队”的车辆，用大灯照了半岛台的摄像机后，将其撞倒<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ksdk.com/videos/news/local/2014/08/14/14042891/ |title=RAW video of Al Jazeera America crews hit with tear gas |publisher=KSDK |date= |accessdate=2014-08-15}}</ref>。

弗格森警察局长否认压制任何媒体。美国总统[[奥巴马|奥巴马]]认为这侵犯了《[[美国宪法第一修正案|美国宪法第一修正案]]》，称“警察过度使用武力对付和平抗议是没有借口可言的，将抗议者送进监狱是依法行使修正案的权利，但在美利坚合众国，本分工作的记者，是向美国人民报道他们所看到的事，警方不应该侮辱或逮捕他们<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2014/08/14/statement-president |title=Statement by the President | The White House |publisher=The White House |date=2013-04-01 |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140815111306/http://www.whitehouse.gov/the-press-office/2014/08/14/statement-president |archive-date=2014-08-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

圣路易斯市议员安东尼奥·法兰奇，在社交媒体记录了抗议活动，周三晚上就遭到警方逮捕<ref name="nytanon">{{cite news|last1=Bosman|first1=Julie|first2=Michael D.|last2=Shear|first3=Timothy|last3=Williams|title=Obama Calls for Open Inquiry Into Police Shooting of Teenager in Ferguson, Mo|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/15/us/ferguson-missouri-police-shooting.html|work=The New York Times|date=2014-08-14|accessdate=2014-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821094559/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/15/us/ferguson-missouri-police-shooting.html|archive-date=2014-08-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。法兰其表示，他钻进车子，逃离警方发射的催泪瓦斯和烟雾弹。尽管他待在自己的车子，却被走近的警察拖下车，最终因非法集会被逮捕。周四从监狱释放后，他向记者表示，有数十人被“维稳部队”逮捕。“监狱里头遍布维稳人员，”他表示，“他们围捕了错人······有牧师、和平的青年团体<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/14/live-updates-on-police-shooting-in-ferguson-mo/ |title=Live Updates on Protests Over Police Shooting in Ferguson, Mo |work=The New York Times |date=2014-08-14 |access-date=2014-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140827064126/http://news.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/08/14/live-updates-on-police-shooting-in-ferguson-mo/ |archive-date=2014-08-27 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Stieber|first1=Zachary|title=Antonio * Local politicians – French, Alderman in St Louis, Arrested in Ferguson, MO Protests (+Videos)|url=http://www.theepochtimes.com/n3/875545-antonio-french-alderman-in-st-louis-arrested-in-ferguson-mo-protests-videos/|accessdate=2014-08-14|newspaper=The Epoch Times|date=2014-08-14|ref=Epoch Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140816204356/http://www.theepochtimes.com/n3/875545-antonio-french-alderman-in-st-louis-arrested-in-ferguson-mo-protests-videos/|archive-date=2014-08-16|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/15/us/protest-in-missouri-at-police-killing-of-teenager-is-chronicled-on-social-media.html|title = Protest in Missouri at Police Killing of Teenager Is Chronicled on Social Media|last = Southall|first = Ashley|date = 2014-08-14|work = |accessdate = 2014-08-14|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140814145902/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/15/us/protest-in-missouri-at-police-killing-of-teenager-is-chronicled-on-social-media.html|archive-date = 2014-08-14|dead-url = no}}</ref>。”

新闻自由记者委员会、媒体和新闻自由大联盟，致信弗格森镇警察部队，抗议骚乱报道抗议活动的记者<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mirkinson|first1=Jack|title=News Coalition Condemns Police Treatment Of Journalists In Ferguson|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/15/police-journalists-ferguson-protest_n_5683125.html|publisher=The Huffington Post|accessdate=2014-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140817070145/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/15/police-journalists-ferguson-protest_n_5683125.html|archive-date=2014-08-17|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Police detention of journalists in Ferguson, Missouri, and public access to information|url=http://www.rcfp.org/sites/default/files/2014-08-15-Ferguson-media-coalition-letter.pdf|publisher=Reporters Committee for Freedom of Press|access-date=2014-08-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902042825/http://www.rcfp.org/sites/default/files/2014-08-15-Ferguson-media-coalition-letter.pdf|archive-date=2014-09-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===8月14日===
[[File:Ferguson,_Day_4,_Photo_26.png|thumb]]
密苏里州美国联邦参议员克莱尔·麦卡斯基尔表示：“警方军事化回应抗议者持续升温<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/video/nbc-news/55867114#55866941 |title=McCaskill: Police 'Militarization' Escalated Unrest In Ferguson – Video on |publisher=NBC News |date= |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140815045033/http://www.nbcnews.com/video/nbc-news/55867114/#55866941 |archive-date=2014-08-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”圣路易斯警察总长山姆·多特森表示，不会采用被透露的军事手段维护治安。多特森表示，“我的直觉告诉我，我所看到的，不是城市中战术，我是从来不会把部下置于那种境地的。”多特森不愿让各显警察局联手的原因，是县警方种族歧视的历史。在发给对种族定性表示关注市议员的电邮中，他写道：“我同意取消我们的战术协助。周二或周三晚，我们没有向弗格森派遣战术资源。我们唯一的增援是四名协助疏导交通，确保行人和司机安全的交警。上周四，我们没有警察协助弗格森<ref>{{cite news |date=2014-08-14 |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/14/ferguson-military-tactics_n_5679532.html |title=St. Louis Police Chief Condemns Military Tactics Being Used In Ferguson |publisher=The Huffington Post |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140815053356/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/14/ferguson-military-tactics_n_5679532.html |archive-date=2014-08-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

密苏里州州长杰伊·尼克松在记者招待会上表示，密苏里州国家高速路巡警，将接管战术遭到广泛批评的圣路易斯县警察，指出变化会是“行动换位”，警方只在必要时采取武力，一般会退让<ref name="nytanon" />。尼克松称，公路巡警队长罗恩·约翰逊，将监督弗格森镇的安全。美国黑人约翰逊，称自己在社区中长大，“对我而言，这意味着很多，我们要打破暴力循环<ref>{{cite news|title=Missouri troopers to take over Ferguson security|url=http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/local/ozarks/2014/08/14/missouri-troopers-to-take-over-ferguson-security/14071993/|agency=Associated Press|newspaper=Springfield News-Leader|accessdate=2014-08-15|date=2014-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819110726/http://www.news-leader.com/story/news/local/ozarks/2014/08/14/missouri-troopers-to-take-over-ferguson-security/14071993/|archive-date=2014-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。”尼克松又称，“弗格森人希望他们的街道远离恐吓和恐惧，但过去几天里，它变得有点像战场，这不能被接受<ref name="nytanon" />。”圣路易斯县检察官罗伯特·P·麦卡洛克批评州长的决定，称“他今天的所为可耻，没有这样做的法律效力，贬低了县警察局的男女干警<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/gov-nixon-gives-police-control-of-ferguson-situation-to-missouri/article_0806541b-ed48-5d06-9267-323531ad6cf1.html |title=McCulloch blasts Nixon for replacing St. Louis County Police control : News |newspaper=St. Louis Post-Dispatch |date=2014-08-11 |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820203941/http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/gov-nixon-gives-police-control-of-ferguson-situation-to-missouri/article_0806541b-ed48-5d06-9267-323531ad6cf1.html |archive-date=2014-08-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。”

8月14日傍晚时分，约翰逊上尉在弗格森组织了大规模的和平游行<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/14/ron-johnson-ferguson_n_5680351.html?utm_hp_ref=canada&ir=Canada |title=New Ferguson Police Commander Ron Johnson Walks With Protesters |publisher=The Huffington Post |date=2014-08-07 |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819090154/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/14/ron-johnson-ferguson_n_5680351.html?utm_hp_ref=canada&ir=Canada |archive-date=2014-08-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/capt-ron-johnson-marches-protesters-ferguson-article-1.1904210 |title=Capt. Ron Johnson marches with protesters in Ferguson as law enforcement scales back on day 5 of turmoil after Michael Brown shooting |newspaper=Daily News (New York) |location=New York |date=2009-03-29 |accessdate=2014-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140815023814/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/capt-ron-johnson-marches-protesters-ferguson-article-1.1904210 |archive-date=2014-08-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=== 8月15日 ===
弗格森警察局长汤姆·杰克逊公布涉及上周五枪击案的警员名单。当天距布朗被警察枪杀快一周。杰克逊公布名单前，称几分钟前在附近的便利店“弗格森酒市场”（Ferguson Market & Liquor）开火的抢劫犯是“铁腕”。警方报告在新闻发布会上公布。报告指出布朗是抢劫犯罪的嫌疑人<ref name=ABC.Public/>。几小时后，杰克逊再次举行记招，称威尔逊拦下布朗时，不知道抢劫的事<ref name=WSJ.Suspect/>。

周五晚，抗议活动以“几乎是庆祝的方式”，在QuikTrip旁继续<ref name="auto2">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/ferguson-during-friday-police-standoff-protesters-try-stop-looters-entering-stores-1660418 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140902052426/http://www.ibtimes.com/ferguson-during-friday-police-standoff-protesters-try-stop-looters-entering-stores-1660418 |archive-date=2014-09-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://stlouis.cbslocal.com/2014/08/16/clean-up-underway-after-more-rioting-looting-in-ferguson/ |title=Clean-Up Underway After More Rioting, Looting In Ferguson « CBS St. Louis |publisher=Stlouis.cbslocal.com |date=2014-08-16 |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819044305/http://stlouis.cbslocal.com/2014/08/16/clean-up-underway-after-more-rioting-looting-in-ferguson/ |archive-date=2014-08-19 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，直至晚上11点警方抵达<ref name="auto2"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://stlouis.cbslocal.com/2014/08/16/clean-up-underway-after-more-rioting-looting-in-ferguson/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819044305/http://stlouis.cbslocal.com/2014/08/16/clean-up-underway-after-more-rioting-looting-in-ferguson/ |archive-date=2014-08-19 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。星期六深夜1:30左右，暴徒闯入并洗劫“弗格森酒市场”，布朗遇害前曾抢劫过那里，此外还有其他商家。起初商店被闯入，一群示威者和围观者，聚集在附近商家的店面，试图阻止进一步的闯入<ref>{{cite web |author=By |url=http://www.ibtimes.com/ferguson-during-friday-police-standoff-protesters-try-stop-looters-entering-stores-1660418 |title=Ferguson: During Friday Police Standoff, Protesters Try To Stop Looters Entering Stores |publisher=Ibtimes.com |date=2014-08-16 |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819090752/http://www.ibtimes.com/ferguson-during-friday-police-standoff-protesters-try-stop-looters-entering-stores-1660418 |archive-date=2014-08-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
===8月16日===
由于昨晚的抢劫和破坏，尼克松在记招上宣布紧急状态，从午夜到凌晨5点，全镇实施夜间宵禁。有居民在新闻发布会上表示，执法人员被暴力的军事战术有煽动性<ref name=CNN.Curfew/>。约翰逊表示，警方不会强制采用装甲车和催泪弹宵禁，而是与示威者沟通，让他们有时间和机会在宵禁前离场<ref name="auto1">{{cite news|title=Governor declares emergency, sets Ferguson curfew|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/gov-declares-emergency-imposes-curfew-ferguson|work=Associated Press|accessdate=2014-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140817085000/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/gov-declares-emergency-imposes-curfew-ferguson|archive-date=2014-08-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===8月17日===
清晨，有警员违反先前的承诺，携带催泪瓦斯出动，枪杀一名示威者致其重伤。警方表示没有开火。另有七人被捕。当天上午，密苏里州高速公路巡警发言人宣布，宵禁延长至第二天<ref name="auto1"/>。

===8月18日===
鉴于宵禁期间的暴力冲突，尼克松发出行政命令，要求[[国民警卫队|国民警卫队]]“协助恢复和平秩序，保护弗格森公民<ref>{{cite web|last1=Hartmann|first1=Margaret|title=National Guard Deployed After Chaotic, Violent Night in Ferguson|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/08/national-guard-called-after-more-ferguson-chaos.html|publisher=NY Magazine|accessdate=2014-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819102937/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2014/08/national-guard-called-after-more-ferguson-chaos.html|archive-date=2014-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>”。尼克松另宣布，当日晚上取消宵禁<ref name=WashPost.MondayCurfew />。[[国际特赦组织|国际特赦组织]]派出13名人权活动家组成的队伍，寻求与官员会面，教导当地活动者非暴力抗争的方法<ref name=Reuters.Amnesty>{{cite web|last1=Wulfhorst|first1=Ellen|title=National Guard called to Missouri town roiled by police shooting of teen|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/08/18/us-usa-missouri-shooting-idUSKBN0GF0LP20140818|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=2014-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140818014125/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/08/18/us-usa-missouri-shooting-idUSKBN0GF0LP20140818|archive-date=2014-08-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。警方命令媒体离开<ref>"Media do not pass us, you're getting maced next time you pass us."</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Gabrielle Bluestone |url=http://gawker.com/ferguson-police-threaten-to-shoot-reporter-and-mace-chr-1623125660 |title=Cops in Ferguson Threaten to Shoot Reporter, Mace Chris Hayes |publisher=Gawker.com |date=2014-08-18 |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821011257/http://gawker.com/ferguson-police-threaten-to-shoot-reporter-and-mace-chr-1623125660 |archive-date=2014-08-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。摄影记者斯科特·奥尔森被警方逮捕<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/18/getty-photographer-arrested_n_5689614.html |title=Getty Photographer Scott Olson Arrested At Ferguson Protest (UPDATED) |publisher=Huffingtonpost.com |date=2014-08-18 |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821034800/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/08/18/getty-photographer-arrested_n_5689614.html |archive-date=2014-08-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在听取总检察长埃里克·霍尔德汇报事件后，奥巴马派遣特使前往弗格森监察骚乱<ref name=UsaToday.Holder>{{cite web|last1=Jaclson|first1=David|title=Obama sending Holder to Ferguson, claims progress in Iraq|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2014/08/18/obama-iraq-ferguson-white-house-eric-holder-national-security-council/14224457/|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=2014-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819093613/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2014/08/18/obama-iraq-ferguson-white-house-eric-holder-national-security-council/14224457/|archive-date=2014-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

当日晚间，数百万示威者中，有人向警方人墙投掷酒瓶，警方遂与民众推搡，有神职人员及社区领袖被顶住武器，才避免对抗升级<ref name=ABCNews.Averting>{{cite web|title=Michael Brown Protest: Crowd Surges Toward Police in Ferguson|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/michael-brown-shooting/michael-brown-protest-crowd-surges-toward-police-ferguson-n183611|publisher=ABC News|accessdate=2014-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819034858/http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/michael-brown-shooting/michael-brown-protest-crowd-surges-toward-police-ferguson-n183611|archive-date=2014-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。78人被逮捕，包括上前解围的莱恩·迪威洛<ref>{{cite web |last=Cook |first=John |url=https://firstlook.org/theintercept/2014/08/19/intercept-reporter-detained-covering-ferguson-protests/ |title=Intercept Reporter Shot With Rubber Bullets and Arrested While Covering Ferguson Protests - The Intercept |publisher=Firstlook.org |date= |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140822035824/https://firstlook.org/theintercept/2014/08/19/intercept-reporter-detained-covering-ferguson-protests/ |archive-date=2014-08-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。德国记者安斯加尔·格劳和弗兰克·赫尔曼，据报被一名称自己为“唐老鸭”的身份不明的警告逮捕<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thelocal.de/20140819/german-journalists-held-in-ferguson-unrest |title=German journalists arrested in Ferguson - The Local |publisher=Thelocal.de |date= |accessdate=2014-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821150400/http://www.thelocal.de/20140819/german-journalists-held-in-ferguson-unrest |archive-date=2014-08-21 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===暂告段落===
[[File:Lesley_McSpadden.jpg|250px]]
8月20日，司法部长[[埃里克·霍尔德|埃里克·霍尔德]]前往弗格森，慰问当地居民及布朗的家人<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-28868389 |title=BBC News - Michael Brown killing: Eric Holder meets teen's family |publisher=BBC |date=2014-08-20 |accessdate=2014-08-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823175640/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-28868389 |archive-date=2014-08-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。相比前晚逮捕了47人，当天仅有六人被捕<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/americas/40984-140821-ferguson-protests-cool-after-holder-s-visit |title=Ferguson protests cool down after Holder's visit | i24news - See beyond |publisher=I24news.tv |date= |accessdate=2014-08-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826130419/http://www.i24news.tv/en/news/international/americas/40984-140821-ferguson-protests-cool-after-holder-s-visit |archivedate=2014-08-26 }}</ref> 。目睹了社会局势的改善后，8月21日，尼克松从弗格森撤回国民警卫队<ref name=Philly.Nixon/>。8月23日，抗议活动和平持续，但有三人被捕<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/08/24/us-usa-missouri-shooting-idUSKBN0GF0LP20140824|title=Calm holds in streets of Ferguson, Missouri two weeks after police shooting|work=www.reuters.com|date=2014-08-24|accessdate=2014-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140824124725/http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/08/24/us-usa-missouri-shooting-idUSKBN0GF0LP20140824|archive-date=2014-08-24|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同一天，在“我是达伦·威尔逊”的支持旗号下，50-70人在弗格森集会<ref name="BF.ThisIs Why">{{cite web|last1=Dalrymple II|first1=Jim|title=This Is Why Darren Wilson Supporters Are Rallying In St. Louis|url=http://www.buzzfeed.com/jimdalrympleii/why-darren-wilson-supporters-are-rallying-in-st-louis|publisher=BuzzFeed|accessdate=2014-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140827080528/http://www.buzzfeed.com/jimdalrympleii/why-darren-wilson-supporters-are-rallying-in-st-louis|archive-date=2014-08-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。截至8月25日，支持者在网上[[众筹|众筹]]活动共捐出近40万美元。线上活动也招来众多种族主义者的评论，迫使网站关闭评论<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/ferguson-shooting-nearly-400k-raised-online-for-officer-darren-wilson-who-fatally-shot-michael-brown/|title=Nearly $400,000 raised online for Ferguson cop who fatally shot teen|work=www.cbsnews.com|date=2014-08-25|accessdate=2014-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140825234045/http://www.cbsnews.com/news/ferguson-shooting-nearly-400k-raised-online-for-officer-darren-wilson-who-fatally-shot-michael-brown/|archive-date=2014-08-25|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=WaPo.Thousands>{{cite web|title=Thousands donated to crowdfunding campaign for Darren Wilson, the officer who shot Michael Brown|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/08/22/thousands-donated-to-crowdfunding-campaign-for-darren-wilson-the-officer-who-shot-michael-brown/|publisher=The Washington Post|accessdate=2014-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826012901/http://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2014/08/22/thousands-donated-to-crowdfunding-campaign-for-darren-wilson-the-officer-who-shot-michael-brown/|archive-date=2014-08-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

为尊重葬礼程序，布朗的家人让支持者8月25日当天停止抗议。“我希望明天是和平的，好让我们的儿子安息。拜托了，这是我的请求，”布朗的父亲表示<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-28924099|title=Michael Brown's father calls for peace ahead of funeral|date=2014-08-25|accessdate=2014-08-25|newspaper=BBC|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140825092839/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-28924099|archive-date=2014-08-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>。该活动得到数千人响应，2500人挤满避难所，教堂有人被挤出去。据估计，两千多人到教堂参加葬礼。布朗的堂兄弟埃里克·戴维斯在葬礼上表示：“去投票吧，让你的声音被听到，让大家知道，我们已经受够了这一切<ref name=KCS.mourners>{{cite news|last1=Suhr|first1=Jim|title=Mourners urge black Americans to take action|url=http://www.kansascity.com/news/state/missouri/article1290626.html#storylink=cpy|publisher=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=2014-08-26|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140826114854/http://www.kansascity.com/news/state/missouri/article1290626.html#storylink=cpy|archivedate=2014-08-26}}</ref>！”

=== 抗议再起：11月24日 ===
在[[密苏里州|密苏里州]]大陪审团决定不起诉涉事警察达伦·威尔逊当天，数百名聚在弗格森市警察局门前等待处理结果的当地民众表达了不满，之后再次引发骚乱。愤怒的抗议民众高呼“还我公正”“阻止种族主义凶手”等口号聚集游行，多辆警车及一些沿街店铺被点燃，警察使用了催泪弹驱散人群，当晚在弗格森拘捕了20余名暴力抗议人士。抗议现场甚至传出了枪声，不过警方表示并非他们所为。警方负责人称，相对8月弗格森骚乱期间冲突最严重的一晚，当晚的情况更加严重。

当天[[华盛顿|华盛顿]]、[[纽约|纽约]]、[[波士顿|波士顿]]、[[费城|费城]]、[[克利夫兰|克利夫兰]]、[[匹兹堡|匹兹堡]]、[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]、[[洛杉矶|洛杉矶]]、[[西雅图|西雅图]]等城市当天也爆发示威活动，抗议圣路易斯县大陪审团作出对白人警察威尔逊免予起诉的决定。<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2014-11/25/c_1113401671.htm| title=美国弗格森：争议持续　冲突再起| publisher=新华网| accessdate=2014-11-25| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150416131837/http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2014-11/25/c_1113401671.htm| archivedate=2015-04-16}}</ref>

===11月25日===
华盛顿、纽约、西雅图、洛杉矶等地11月25日晚间有群众聚集表达不满。示威大致和平，但纽约曾一度有人堵塞[[布鲁克林|布鲁克林]]大桥等交通要道。而在经历过一整天骚乱后，密苏里州当局向弗格森增派了2200名国民警卫军人员镇暴。当地25日晚基本平静，不过镇内一段主要马路曾被示威者封堵，也有人在联邦法院大楼外集会，镇内示威者至26日凌晨仍未散去。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2014/11-26/6818685.shtml | title=美国弗格森枪击案示威持续 涉事警察首次受访 | publisher=中国新闻网 | accessdate=2014-11-26 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141130121945/http://www.chinanews.com/gj/2014/11-26/6818685.shtml | archive-date=2014-11-30 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

